info.description: Documentation of the BioThings SEMMEDDB query web services.
info.title: BioThings SEMMEDDB API

ids.description: multiple association IDs separated by comma. Note that currently we only take the input ids up to 1000 maximum, the rest will be omitted. Type: string (list). Max: 1000.

200.description: A list of matching association objects

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

post.summary: For a list of association IDs, return the matching disease object

parameters.description: Retrieve association objects based on Association ID  Supports JSONP and CORS as well.
parameters.name: associationid

404.description: A response indicating an unknown association ID

get.summary: Retrieve association objects based on ID
Get metadata about the data available from the API
Get metadata about the data fields available

200.description: A query response with the "hits" property

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

get.summary: Make queries and return matching association hits. Supports JSONP and CORS as well.

q.description: multiple query terms separated by comma (also "+" or whitespace).  Does not support wildcard queries

scopes.description: a comma-separated list of fields as the search "scopes" (fields to search through for query term). The available "fields" that can be passed to the "scopes" parameter are listed in the **/metadata/fields** endpoint.string Default: "scopes=_id".

200.description: Query response objects with the "hits" property

400.description: A response indicating an improperly formatted query

post.summary: Make batch disease queries and return matching disease hits

callback.description: you can pass a "callback" parameter to make a JSONP call. Type: string.
callback.name: callback

dotfield.description: control the format of the returned chem object. If "true" or "1", all fields will be collapsed into a single level deep object (all nested objects will be a single level deep, using dotfield notation to signify the nested structure) Type: boolean. Default: false.
dotfield.name: dotfield

email.description: If you are regular users of our services, we encourage you to provide us with an email, so that we can better track the usage or follow up with you.
email.name: email

facet_size.description: the number of facet buckets to return in the response. Type: integer. Default: 10. Max: 1000.
facet_size.name: facet_size

facets.description: a comma-separated list of fields to return facets on.  In addition to query hits, the fields notated in "facets" will be aggregated by value and bucklet counts will be displayed in the "facets" field of the response object. Type: string (list). Default: None. Max: 1000.
facets.name: facets

fields.description: a comma-separated list of fields (in dotfield notation) used to limit the fields returned from the matching chem hit(s). The supported field names can be found from any chem object or from the /metadata/fields endpoint. If "fields=all", all available fields will be returned. Type: string (list). Default: all. Max: 1000.
fields.name: fields

format.description: controls output format of server response, currently supports: "json", "jsonld", "html". Type: string. Default: json.
format.name: format

from.description: the number of matching chem hits to skip, starting from 0.  This can be useful for paging in combination with the "size" parameter. Type: integer. Default: None.
from.name: from

prefix.description: Pass a prefix string to filter the available fields. Type: string. Default: None.
prefix.name: prefix

search.description: Pass a search term to filter the available fields. Type: string. Default: None.
search.name: search

size.description: the maximum number of matching chem hits to return per batch. Type: integer. Default: 10.
size.name: size

sort.description: the comma-separated list of fields to sort on. Prefix each with "-" for descending order, otherwise in ascending order. Default: sort by descending score.
sort.name: sort
